  "text": "Sediment handling and experimental setup. Sediment was collected in September 2006 at 2 sites located along the west coast of the island of Fyn, Denmark. Sediment consisting of medium sand with a low content of Fe and OM was collected at Svenstrup Strand (Fe-poor), while sediment with similar grain size structure, but relatively rich in Fe and OM, was collected at Odden (Fe-rich) close to Faenø Sund. The 2 sites are situated < 5 km apart and share the same body of water. Location of sampling sites can be seen in [CITATION_1] . At each site, 9 undisturbed sediment cores containing the natural benthic fauna were collected in shallow water (about 1 m depth) with Plexiglas core liners (inner diameter [i.d.] 8 cm) that were sealed at both ends with rubber stoppers. Additionally, subsamples of the upper 10 cm sediment for the determination of grain size and average sediment characteristics were collected at each site, sieved through 1 mm mesh and homogenized by hand. Water temperature and salinity on the day of sampling were 15°C and 20, respectively, at both sites.",
